conquer /ˈkɒŋkə/

(conquering,conquered,conquers) 

1. V-T If one country or group of people conquers another, they take complete control of their land. 征服; 攻占 

例： During 1936, Mussolini conquered Abyssinia. 1936年墨索里尼攻占了阿比西尼亚。 

2. V-T If you conquer something such as a problem, you succeed in ending it or dealing with it successfully. 克服 

例： I was certain that love was quite enough to conquer our differences. 我确信爱颇足以消除我们的分歧。 

例： He has never conquered his addiction to smoking. 他从未戒除过烟瘾。

